nges.\\n- `audit_log` table: id, actorId, actorRole, action enum, targetType, targetId, beforePayload (JSON), afterPayload (JSON), timestamp, ipAddress.\\n- Audit records are append-only and immutable.\\n- `GET /api/audit-log?targetType=&targetId=&actorId=&action=&from=&to=` — query audit log (admin only, or scoped to own actions for IC/manager).\\n\\n**Snapshot immutability verification:**\\n- Add integrity checks: lock snapshots and reconcile snapshots cannot be modified after creation.\\n- Database-level: no UPDATE/DELETE permissions on snapshot tables for application user (or application-level write-once enforcement).\\n\\n**Idempotency verification:**\\n- Review all lifecycle jobs (auto-lock, reconcile-open, read-model refresh) for idempotency.\\n- Add guards: check current state before transition, use optimistic locking, verify no duplicate snapshots or carry-forward links on retry.\\n\\n**Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA):**\\n- Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements focusable and operable via keyboard.\\n- Commit reorder: ensure keyboard alternative (move-up/move-down buttons) works correctly with screen readers.\\n- ARIA labels on all icon-only buttons, status badges, and interactive elements.\\n- Color independence: chess piece types, plan states, risk flags, and outcomes distinguishable without color alone (icons, text labels, patterns).\\n- Focus management: modal dialogs trap focus, return focus on close.\\n- Form error announcements: validation errors announced to screen readers.\\n\\n**Integration verification:**\\n- End-to-end flow tests (unit test level): create plan → add commits → lock → scope change → reconcile → carry-forward. Verify snapshots, events, and state transitions.\\n- Verify permission boundaries: IC cannot access other's plans, peer sees only basic detail, manager sees full detail for directs.\\n- Verify AI degradation: disable AI provider, confirm all core flows complete successfully.\\n- Performance spot-checks: verify derived rea