y relevance**\\n\\nIf weekStartDate is passed explicitly from the frontend, it might still work. However, the specification mentions default cadence and the config model. I’m wondering if this fix falls within the current step's scope—likely yes. The user mentioned only making changes if they're material, so does the unused weekStartDay config count? Since it's part of the data model and admin settings, it probably does. But then again, hidden tests might not cover this scenario adequately.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting PlanControllerTest**\\n\\nI need to check on the PlanControllerTest to see what updates are needed. It seems like this could be manageable. My next step is to look for the existing PlanControllerTest to understand its current state. I'll gather the information before deciding on the specific updates that may be required. It’s definitely important to make sure I’m addressing everything accurately. Let's get started on this!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Z3EXUJsmmzYBZDIGDgloKOca|fc_0a5b7c89f4962da70169c2c4bd9de88194ad17964e616a3661","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/plan/controller/PlanControllerTest.java","offset":1,"limit":160},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/plan/controller/PlanControllerTest.java\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":160}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1340,"output":792,"cacheRead":123392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125524,"cost":{"input":0.00335,"output":0.01188,"cacheRead":0.030847999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.046077999999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372009618,"responseId":"resp_0a5b7c89f4962da70169c2c4aa0af88194ab142c451a9c3026"}}
