 any frontend files.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Reviewed the Step 19 backend diff, mainly:\n- `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/config/**`\n- `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/domain/entity/OrgConfig.java`\n- `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/domain/entity/TeamConfigOverride.java`\n- `backend/src/main/resources/db/migration/V7__add_org_config.sql`\n- `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/plan/service/WeeklyPlanService.java`\n- related tests in `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/config/**` and `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/plan/service/WeeklyPlanServiceTest.java`\n\nWhat I changed:\n- Fixed missing configuration model fields:\n  - added `draft_open_offset_hours` to `org_config`\n  - added `week_start_day` and `draft_open_offset_hours` to `team_config_override`\n  - wired those fields through entities, DTOs, merge logic, and tests\n- Fixed a lifecycle bug in `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/config/service/ConfigurationService.java`:\n  - `computeReconcileDeadline(...)` was using `reconcileDueOffsetHours`\n  - it now uses `reconcileOpenOffsetHours`, so reconcile opening aligns with Friday 17:00 instead of next Monday\n- Fixed a capacity resolution bug:\n  - `getEffectiveCapacity(...)` now throws `ResourceNotFoundException` for unknown users instead of incorrectly returning the system default\n- Updated backend tests accordingly:\n  - `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/config/service/ConfigurationServiceTest.java`\n  - `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/plan/service/WeeklyPlanServiceTest.java`\n\nChecks run:\n- `npm run lint`\n- `npm run typecheck`\n- `npm run unit`\n- `npm run build`\n\nAssessment:\n- I found material backend defects in the Step 19 implementation and fixed them.\n- All required checks now pass.\n\n```observations\n- [medium] backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/plan/controller/PlanController.java: When `weekStartDate` is omitted, the controller still defaults via `WeeklyPlanService.currentWeekStart()` (hardcoded Monday/UTC), so configured `weekStartDay`/timezone does not yet influence implicit current-week resolution.\n- [medium] backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/config/service/ConfigurationService.java: `draftOpenOffsetHours` is now modeled and exposed, but no current backend workflow consumes it yet.\n- [low] backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/config/controller/: There are still no controller-level tests for `ConfigController`.\n```\n\nVerdict: changes_made","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a5b7c89f4962da70169c2c4df00188194bcc21e3e470a41bb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1376,"output":1974,"cacheRead":125440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128790,"cost":{"input":0.0034400000000000003,"output":0.02961,"cacheRead":0.03136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.06441}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372030032,"responseId":"resp_0a5b7c89f4962da70169c2c4becac48194b2f21877264e66e9"}}
+{"type":"message","id":"601407a0","parentId":"b8ea4594","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:25:33.893Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Operator notes for this run:\n## Operator note — 2026-03-24T14:22:02.774Z\n\nThis step is BACKEND ONLY. Do NOT touch any frontend files. Work exclusively in backend/src/. You must: (1) Create Flyway migration V3__add_ticket_priority.sql, (2) Add TicketPriority\n │ enum, PagedTicketResponse, TicketDetailResponse, TicketSummaryResponse, LinkedCommitEntry, CreateTicketFromCommitRequest records, (3) Add paginated/filterable ticket list endpoint, (4)\n │ Add /api/tickets/summaries endpoint, (5) Add /api/tickets/from-commit endpoint, (6) Add /api/users/{userId}/plan-history endpoint, (7) Add /api/teams/{teamId}/history endpoint, (8) Add\n │ /api/commits/{commitId}/carry-forward-lineage alias. All work in Java backend only. The frontend files already exist and should NOT be modified in this step\n\nThese notes are authoritative user steering for this run. Follow them unless they directly conflict with the repository state or the controller's explicit task.\n\nPlan overview:\n{\n  \"goal\": \"Build the Weekly Commit Module v1 — a production micro-frontend (TypeScript/React) with Java 21 modular-monolith backend replacing 15Five for weekly planning. Implements structured weekly commitments with RCDO strategy linkage, chess-layer prioritization, lock/reconcile lifecycle with immutable snapshots, explicit carry-forward with provenance, native tickets with status workflow, manager team dashboard with exception review, conservative explainable AI assistance, rules-based notifications, derived read models for reporting, and comprehensive audit logging. Delivered as a route-level Module Federation remote integrated into the PA host app. Note: The PRD recommends Java 21 (§22) and all checks are npm-based; the monorepo root package.json orchestrates both the TypeScript frontend (Vite/React) and Java backend (Gradle) via shell-out scripts. SQL migrations use Flyway against PostgreSQL.\",\n  \"totalSteps\": 20,\n  \"stepTitles\": [\n    \"1. Monorepo scaffolding and build infrastructure\",\n    \"2. Domain model types, enums, and database schema\",\n    \"3. RCDO hierarchy management API\",\n    \"4. Weekly plan creation and commit CRUD API\",\n    \"5. Lock lifecycle and baseline snapshot API\",\n    \"6. Post-lock scope change and reconciliation API\",\n    \"7. Carry-forward and ticket/work item API\",\n    \"8. Team weekly view, manager review, and permissions API\",\n    \"9. Frontend micro-frontend setup and routing\",\n    \"10. RCDO management UI\",\n    \"11. My Week page with commit list and capacity meter\",\n    \"12. Lock flow and reconcile view UI\",\n    \"13. Team Week dashboard UI\",\n    \"14. Backend ticket and supplementary API contract alignment\",\n    \"15. Frontend ticket contract alignment and Tickets UI completion\",\n    \"16. Notifications backend and frontend panel\",\n    \"17. AI provider abstraction, commit assistance, and risk detection\",\n    \"18. Derived read models and operational reporting\",\n    \"19. Configuration management and admin settings\",\n    \"20. Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\"\n  ]\n}\n\nStep 20: Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-20\",\n  \"title\": \"Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\",\n  \"description\": \"Implement comprehensive audit logging (PRD §13 FR-11), accessibility (PRD §24), and final integration polish.\\n\\n**Audit logging (backend):**\\n- `AuditLogService`: records all auditable events with actor, action, target, timestamp, before/after payload.\\n- Auditable events: plan state transitions (create, lock, auto-lock, reconcile-open, reconcile-submit), commit CRUD, scope change events, carry-forward actions, RCDO create/update/archive/move, ticket status changes, capacity overrides, manager comments, AI suggestion create/feedback, admin config changes.\\n- `audit_log` table: id, actorId, actorRole, action enum, targetType, targetId, beforePayload (JSON), afterPayload (JSON), timestamp, ipAddress.\\n- Audit records are append-only and immutable.\\n- `GET /api/audit-log?targetType=&targetId=&actorId=&action=&from=&to=` — query audit log (admin only, or scoped to own actions for IC/manager).\\n\\n**Snapshot immutability verification:**\\n- Add integrity checks: lock snapshots and reconcile snapshots cannot be modified after creation.\\n- Database-level: no UPDATE/DELETE permissions on snapshot tables for application user (or application-level write-once enforcement).\\n\\n**Idempotency verification:**\\n- Review all lifecycle jobs (auto-lock, reconcile-open, read-model refresh) for idempotency.\\n- Add guards: check current state before transition, use optimistic locking, verify no duplicate snapshots or carry-forward links on retry.\\n\\n**Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA):**\\n- Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements focusable and operable via keyboard.\\n- Commit reorder: ensure keyboard alternative (move-up/move-down buttons) works correctly with screen readers.\\n- ARIA labels on all icon-only buttons, status badges, and interactive elements.\\n- Color independence: chess piece types, plan states, risk flags, and outcomes distinguishable without color alone (icons, text labels, patterns).\\n- Focus management: modal dialogs trap focus, return focus on close.\\n- Form error announcements: validation errors announced to screen readers.\\n\\n**Integration verification:**\\n- End-to-end flow tests (unit test level): create plan → add commits → lock → scope change → reconcile → carry-forward. Verify snapshots, events, and state transitions.\\n- Verify permission boundaries: IC cannot access other's plans, peer sees only basic detail, manager sees full detail for directs.\\n- Verify AI degradation: disable AI provider, confirm all core flows complete successfully.\\n- Performance spot-checks: verify derived read model queries are used for dashboard endpoints.\\n\\n**Unit tests:** audit log records all event types with correct payloads, snapshot immutability enforced, lifecycle job idempotency (double-run produces no duplicates), accessibility attributes present on key components, end-to-end flow produces correct state transitions and snapshots, permission boundaries enforced.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nThis is relay round 2. Another agent has already worked on this step.\n\nYou are in VERIFICATION MODE. Your default action is to APPROVE.\nFocus your review on the DIFF — the changes made in the previous round.\nOnly make changes if there is a MATERIAL defect: failing check, missing step requirement, logic bug, or security issue.\nStyle preferences, alternative approaches, comment wording, and optional polish are NOT grounds for changes.\n\nIf all checks pass and the step requirements are met, approve immediately.\nLog anything else you notice as observations — do not act on them.\n\nPrevious agent's notes:\nAll the operator note requirements from step 14 that were \"not yet implemented\" are now confirmed to exist:\n- ✅ V3__add_ticket_priority.sql (already existed from step 14)\n- ✅ TicketPriority enum (already existed)\n- ✅ PagedTicketResponse (already existed)\n- ✅ TicketDetailResponse (already existed)\n- ✅ TicketSummaryResponse (already existed)\n- ✅ LinkedCommitEntry (already existed)\n- ✅ CreateTicketFromCommitRequest (already existed)\n- ✅ GET /api/tickets (paginated/filterable, already existed)\n- ✅ GET /api/tickets/summaries (already existed)\n- ✅ POST /api/tickets/from-commit (already existed)\n- ✅ GET /api/users/{userId}/plan-history (already existed from step 14)\n- ✅ GET /api/teams/{teamId}/history (already existed as /api/teams/{id}/history)\n- ✅ GET /api/commits/{commitId}/carry-forward-lineage (already existed)\n\nNow for the **new** step 20 requirements:\n- ✅ V8 migration (V8__add